<section>
  <h2>Panel Sections</h2>
  <p>The panel contains four collapsible <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> sections with exclusive accordion behavior (one open at a time).</p>

  <h3>Appearance</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Color Mode</strong> &mdash; Segmented control: Auto / Light / Dark</li>
    <li><strong>Theme</strong> &mdash; <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> with optgroups: Base (Default), Personality (Modern, Minimal, Classic), and Extreme (Swiss, Brutalist, Cyber, Terminal, Organic, Editorial, Kawaii, 8-Bit, NES, Win9x, Rough)</li>
    <li><strong>Accent Color</strong> &mdash; Row of circular swatches, only visible when "Default" theme is selected. The 10 color themes (Ocean, Forest, Sunset, etc.) are hue variants of Default and are presented here instead of as separate top-level themes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Accessibility</h3>
  <p>Toggle switches (<code>input[data-switch="sm"]</code>) for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>High Contrast</li>
    <li>Large Text</li>
    <li>Dyslexia-Friendly</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Layout</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Fluid Scaling</strong> &mdash; Toggle switch (on/off). When off, static token values are used.</li>
    <li><strong>Density</strong> &mdash; Segmented control (Compact / Default / Spacious), only visible when fluid scaling is enabled.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Effects</h3>
  <p>Toggle switches for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Motion Effects (default: on)</li>
    <li>Sound Effects (default: off)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>A <strong>Reset to Defaults</strong> button in the footer clears all preferences.</p>

  <browser-window
    src="/docs/examples/demos/settings-panel-panels.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/settings/panels"
    title="Settings Panel Sections"
    style="min-height: 32rem;"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>
</section>

